      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe LU-10527 patch is causing failures on MDT failover (recovery aborting), reporting apparent llog corruption.\n\nMessages vary, but this is a common example:\nFeb 22 16:03:22 soak-10 kernel: LustreError: 12847:0:(llog.c:588:llog_process_thread()) soaked-MDT0003-osp-MDT0002: [0x1:0xc002abb4:0x2] Invalid record: index 4 but expected 2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "f60799d23097f59b755b62d684d917e1f9f47271",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
