      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-28 17:56:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nMore important than the original commit message is why the patch was reverted (eg. link to LU ticket and brief description of the problem that the patch caused).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "95f16a47d1e60a93be2cc69c6f1fb678076f9f0f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-02-28 18:00:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nUnderstood.\n\nHopefully, we won't need this revert at all:\nhttps://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/34346/",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "37d34bd8bbe18902d2c9c47a0cdfe5e5bdbf03c9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-28 18:01:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nJust having the brief description from your comment would be preferable:\n\n Revert \"LU-10527 obdclass: don't recycle loghandle upon ENOSPC\"\n\n This reverts Revert \"LU-10527 obdclass: don't recycle loghandle upon ENOSPC\"\n\n This reverts commit 5761b9576d39c44c02455b86eb86ce1276930e60.  .\n \n The LU-10527 patch is causing failures on MDT failover (recovery\n aborting), reporting apparent llog corruption.\n Messages vary, but this is a common example:\n Feb 22 16:03:22 soak-10 kernel: LustreError: 12847:0:(llog.c:588:llog_process_thread()) soaked-MDT0003-osp-MDT0002: [0x1:0xc002abb4:0x2] Invalid record: index 4 but expected 2",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "926cc1189390d854f69f09df7aa0d597c8caf0d2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2019-02-28 18:51:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nI agree that simply removing the LASSERT(llh) fixes the original problem (LU-10527), and also that the second part of my patch was only intended to limit the impact of llog ENOSPC situation handling.\nOTOH, I don't easily figure out how this can cause llog corruption upon failover ...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "1db32ea68705d5807c99558385ee0f2a9bd7c81a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-02-28 19:28:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks, Bruno\n\nI switched to doing what the commit suggested - removing the assert.  It works with Sergey's reproducer.\n\nCould you review:\nhttps://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/34347/\nAnd:\nhttps://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/34346/\n\nBoth just revert the other part of the patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d78f2cacffb2cb0e7611c8763863674971dc5d56",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-02-28 19:28:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAlso, I agree - I can't see how it's causing issues, but it definitely is.  Perhaps there's more state we need to clean up on ENOSPC?  (And it seems like ENOSPC is getting generated during failover, which is interesting.)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
